On utilise la conversion $1° = \dfrac{\pi}{180}$ rad :
- $30° = 30 \times \dfrac{\pi}{180} = \dfrac{\pi}{6}$ ;
- $45° = 45 \times \dfrac{\pi}{180} = \dfrac{\pi}{4}$ ;
- $120° = 120 \times \dfrac{\pi}{180} = \dfrac{2\pi}{3}$ ;
- $270° = 270 \times \dfrac{\pi}{180} = \dfrac{3\pi}{2}$.

D'après le tableau des valeurs usuelles :
- $\cos\dfrac{\pi}{6} = \dfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$ ;
- $\sin\dfrac{\pi}{4} = \dfrac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$ ;
- $\cos\dfrac{\pi}{2} = 0$ (point image $(0 \, ; \, 1)$) ;
- $\sin\pi = 0$ (point image $(-1 \, ; \, 0)$).
